itemListElement.name: From Seattle: Private Tour to Mt. Rainier

name: From Seattle: Private Tour to Mt. Rainier
description:
Experience the beauty of Mt. Rainier National Park in the comfort of your own private tour. The adventure begins from your hotel, where your personal local expert will pick your party up in a Pearl Chevrolet Suburban LTZ. 

Work with your tour guide to create the best itinerary and stops for your group. See and experience places within the National Park that our public tour cannot reach. Set the tone for the day by leaning more towards an adventure, hiking-filled day or sit back and relax while you enjoy a leisurely, scenic day on the mountain. Its up to you!

For tours November - April, we can only access the roads in the park which do not require chains. These tours often cannot make it to Paradise, Christine or Narada Falls. We offer snow shoes as a replacement as the majority of the tour will take place at Longmire.

itemListElement.name: 5 Hours Private Seattle City Driving Tour

name: 5 Hours Private Seattle City Driving Tour
description:
This Seattle driving tour adventure fits all of the best attractions into five hours, just enough so youll feel youve gotten the Seattle experience!

No visit to Seattle is complete without a Pike Place Market tour, during which well have plenty of time to explore the historic marketplaces maze of shops and stalls. Your tour guide will help you navigate the historic market and discover its best attractions, from the famous flying fish to the notorious Gum Wall. 

Our caffeine fiends will want to take some selfies at the oldest running Starbucks, and foodies will want to grab a bite to eat at local market favorites, with recommendations from your tour guide!

The market has long had ties to the waterfront, which today features numerous souvenir shops, eateries, and spectacular views of the Puget Sound and distant Olympic Mountains. After a leisurely drive along the bay, well head up to Queen Anne, where youll be treated to incredible views of the Space Needle and city skyline.

review.name: Better than an Alaskan cruise??
review.reviewBody: I booked this for my 86 year old parents to burn time between the return of their Alaskan cruise in the am and their flight home in the pm.  I swear they talked more about this Seattle driving tour than they did about the cruise!  My folks have special needs (wheelchair) and the driver treated them with such respect and kindness, showed them a great time and even took them to lunch.  They said he was incredibly knowledgeable about everything.  Five stars!

review.name: 5 hour private Seattle tour with Lee Dunlap from WeVenture
review.reviewBody: It was so wonderful to have Lee pick the 4 of  us and our luggage up at the airport, start the tour by mentioning what we were seeing along the way to city of Seattle ( there was a long traffic back up) , guide us thru the Pike Market (including lunch recommendations), then a trip thru the surrounding Seattle neighborhoods with picture stops at overlook and park.  Then we went to be awed at  Chuhuly museum and finally Lee dropped us off at our 4 Seasons  hotel.  He was charming, had a lot of knowledge about Seattle and  we would highly recommend him as a driver and tour guide.

name: Seattle's Sailing Experience - BYOB!
description: This is a boat ride like nothing else in Seattle! Our 70ft custom built sailboats were created to race around the world, and now are perfectly at home on Puget Sound. Sit back and relax as our trained crew hoist the sails and turn off the engine to get great views of the Seattle city skyline and surrounding mountain ranges. Enjoy your own food and drinks while we cruise around under power of the wind.

review.name: A beautiful May Day.
review.reviewBody: This was very, very fun.  First day of the season and we lucked out - blue skies and 75 degrees!  The captain and crew were so friendly and knowledgeable.  They really took care to see we had a good time.  I'm a local, so planning on doing it again this summer.

review.name: May 1 2025
review.reviewBody: So lovely! The boat is so sturdy and the sailing was smooth.  The crew was kind and friendly and easy to chat with.  The city view is beautiful from the water.

review.name: We had a great adventure!
review.reviewBody: We had a great adventure. Craig and Hannah made a great crew!  The wind was great and the views were awesome! We even saw several rainbows!

review.name: Hop aboard - its good
review.reviewBody: Nice harbor tour with good weather and wind the day I went. Captain and hand on board were very congenial. Recommend the experience.

review.name: Sailing Seattle - Highly Recommend!
review.reviewBody: Our family had an amazing experience sailing with Craig and Bree. We had a chilly sail in October but they brought out warm jackets and blankets for us to use. They were very enjoyable to chat with during the sail, answering all our curiosities about the boat and sailing techniques. We also got a very unexpected treat on our sail - an orca pod sighting! Craig was very knowledgeable about the orcas and their movementsit almost felt like our sail was a whale-watching excursion. I highly recommend taking a sail with Sailing Seattle - and you're extra lucky if you get to spend it with Craig and Bree!

review.name: Wind, waves and sunshine !
review.reviewBody:
Great day for a sail, with sunshine and clouds.  The crew was very welcoming.....and did their best to get a sighting of an Orca pod...that's been spotted recently.  2 thumbs up, we did see the pod.
There was just enough wind to actually sail - awesome ! 
Wonderful way to spend a lazy Sunday afternoon and a great introduction to sailing.

review.name: Frederick Travis and Jonathon Harrell
review.reviewBody:
Amazing staff, prompt and on time. They were very social. It was only 3 passengers on today September 23, 2024 but they made it very entertaining. They explained in detail rules to follow and socialized with us the entire trip. The captain was absolutely amazing. 

-Frederick

review.name: Great tour of the sound
review.reviewBody: Joey and Zoe were great hosts and had great knowledge of the area explaining every single question we had. They were great sailors and tourist guides.

review.name: Incredible afternoon sailboat ride
review.reviewBody:
We had a great time! Just a. Wonderful afternoon with friends. The day was perfect and we got a sense of the family owned, deeply loved family business. Relaxing and just perfect to end our day.
Thank you! Especially Joey and Zoey whom took us on the ride and showed us around.

review.name: Good sailing experience
review.reviewBody: We have been lucky with the weather and this was a lovely late afternoon sailing session. Great experience and really enjoyed it

itemListElement.name: View of Tulips, La Conner, Deception Pass Bridge & Whidbey Island

name: View of Tulips, La Conner, Deception Pass Bridge & Whidbey Island
description:
The colorful tulip fields are beautiful in the Spring in Washington and and the RoozenGaarde tulip garden is a unique experience only in April and beginning May. 
Then you experience visiting La Conner which is a cozy small costal town and the Deception Pass Bridge located on the scenic Whidbey Island - one of the many islands in the Puget Sound. The ferry ride from the island to the mainland is nice way to experience Puget Sound.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Music Small Group Private Walking Tour

name: Seattle Music Small Group Private Walking Tour
description:
Seattle is synonymous with the music of the 90s, but on this walking tour of the city, well discover not only the usual suspects of grunge style but other acts and performance venues that may surprise you!

Well start in Pioneer Square, home to several bars featuring live music, including a historic venue that has hosted the likes of Kurt Cobain and Jimi Hendrix. Along with a background in the areas music history, youll enjoy a little history of the citys founding, evident in its 19th-century brick buildings.

On our Pike Place Market tour segment, we may catch a busker performance and learn about street musicians who got their start here as well as nearby music venues that have played host to renowned artists. 

After a brief pass through the market, we may have time to catch a ride on the monorail to Seattle Center, home of the iconic Space Needle and Museum of Pop Culture. Continue your own music journey by visiting the attractions or head downtown to enjoy some live music!

itemListElement.name: Arthur Murray Dance Studio North Seattle

name: Arthur Murray Dance Studio North Seattle
Snoqualmie Fall & Railway Museum 3-Hours (Private Tour)
description: Experience the best of history and natural beauty with our private tour package! Step back in time at the Northwest Railway Museum in Snoqualmie Historic Town, where you'll explore meticulously restored train cars, vintage locomotives, and immerse yourself in the captivating stories of the railroad's past. Our knowledgeable guide will accompany you, providing fascinating insights and anecdotes along the way. Afterward, we'll whisk you away to the majestic Snoqualmie Falls, where you'll witness the awe-inspiring cascade and feel the mist on your face. Take in the panoramic views from the observation deck and follow the forest trails for a serene nature walk. This exclusive tour promises an unforgettable blend of history, culture, and natural wonders, creating cherished memories that will last a lifetime. Book your private tour now and embark on this remarkable journey through time and nature.

review.name: El mejor tour  en espaol en Seattle
review.reviewBody: El mejor tour en espaol en Seattle! Mario es un increble gua con increbles recomendaciones. Las vistas son preciosas. Vale totalmente la pena!

review.name: Mario es el mejor gua para visitar las cataratas porque te ensea los mejores sitios con encanto y te ayuda en todo.
review.reviewBody: Con Mario, puedes tener increbles  fotografas de recuerdo y aprender mucho de Las cataratas y de Seattle, porque tambin hicimos el Tour con l.

review.name: Un paseo para no perdrselo

Es un paseo hermoso donde uno puede apreciar la naturaleza, hermosos paisajes y pueblos propios del lugar. El museo de los trenes es muy interesantes y pone de manifiesto la importancia de ese medio de locomocin.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Tour 3/4 hours (LUXURY SUV GROUP OF 7 MAXIMUM)

name: Seattle Tour 3/4 hours (LUXURY SUV GROUP OF 7 MAXIMUM)
description:
Get an overview of Seattle on a half-day ( 3 -4 hours) Luxury SUV tour that includes stops at top destinations. Get a closer look at attractions such as the Space Needle, Pioneer Square, Kerry park , and pass by landmarks including Pike Place Market, and Seattles pro baseball and football stadiums. get great photo ops throughout the tour.

Tour ends at the Space Needle. You will have the option to return to downtown Seattle (any hotel around)

review.name: Bad experience
review.reviewBody: The overall service quality was below average. The communication was poor, and the staff didnt seem to care about customer satisfaction. It left a bad impression.

itemListElement.name: Small Group Olympic National Park Day Tour from Seattle 2CanGo

name: Small Group Olympic National Park Day Tour from Seattle 2CanGo
description:
Include most highlights of Olympic National Park during this full-day guided small group tour from Seattle, comfortable vehicle transfers and a ferry ride over the Puget Sound. Discover the park's diverse eco-systems as you explore varied terrains and landscapes. Enjoy the beauty of the great outdoors in the Pacific Northwest. Itineraries vary, but include Hurricane Ridge, Crescent Lake, and Merrymere Fall.

We will take Washingtong State ferry from Seattle to Bainbridge Island in the morning and then drive you from Bainbridge to Olympic National Park and learn about Communitys unique history in details on the way
During the winter months, trek through the beautiful forests with snowshoes
Lunch water and a little snack are provided
Take photos with parks prettiest natural features in one day
Round-trip transfers from a variety of Seattle neighborhoods or the airport are included
Explore the park's best spots by hiking or snowshoeing, depending on the season

review.name: Relaxing and Enjoyable
review.reviewBody: We had an amazing time! Our guide Jennifer was awesome. Small group made it personable and easy to move from place to place. Would do again.

review.name: Olympic National Park tour
review.reviewBody: The ride from Seattle was over 2 hours each way but once you arrive, the mountain views are spectacular. I got to see a black bear and many deers. Lake Crescent was  nice with the short hike to Marymere Falls.

review.name: Wow!!
review.reviewBody: Amazing views!! Great tour!! Loved the nature, great timing with the schedule. Thank you so much for this wonderful day!!

review.name: Good highlights tour and guide
review.reviewBody: I booked this tour and had Jereme as my tour guide. Very nice, understanding, and accommodating to each of those in the group. It is a tour, so keep in mind they have to stay on schedule when it comes to driving time and the ferries too. Not for those looking to explore the whole park. It is for those looking at just the highlights of Olympic National Park. Jereme took the time to pick up and drop us all off, including me who is staying a bit far from Seattle towards the airport area. Cannot express enough how thankful I am to have him as my first tour guide in Seattle by how gracious and kind he is in making his group feel comfortable to enjoy the experience. Jereme is very good and I recommend him for any future tours for those looking to book.

review.name: good experience
review.reviewBody: It was a great pleasure to participate in this tour. The itinerary was reasonably arranged, the tour guide was patient, the driver drove very well, and the scenery was beautiful. I look forward to participating again next time

review.name: Great Tour to Olympic National Park
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful tour! It was a fun ferry ride and amazing sights around and in the Olympic National Park. The rainforest was amazing. Thank you Tony.

review.name: Cool tour
review.reviewBody:
Tour was great! Duan was up front about the sights we would be seeing due to the fact Hurricane Ridge was closed because of the weather and did his absolute best in getting us there and back. He was very kind and knowledgeable about the areas surrounding Olympic Park National park and stopped along the way for us to see the views. 

Once we got to a trail to hike, he explained clearly the way to go and what time to meet back up and pretty much let our group have some time to explore. 

He made sure to accommodate everyone and his driving was safe. 

Would definitely book this again.
